All Star Game

MICHIGAN HIGH SCHOOL ALL STAR GAME

Zach Kohn played for the East squad in 2016. West 8 East 3

Zach pitched a scoreless inning, striking out 1, 2 ground ball outs and a hit batter was the only base runner.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Coach Liptow was an assistant coach in the 2015 All Star Game for the East. The East beat the West 4-3.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Pat Lancaster played in the 2010 High School All-Star Game at Comerica Park. He went 2 for 3 with a triple and pitched a scoreless inning.

Photo Courtesy of Bryan Bosch, Chief Photographer, Monroe Evening News

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Mike Jordan played in the east/west all star game at Tiger Stadium in 1989.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Mike Talbert and John Lefevre represented Carlson in the 1986 all star game at Tiger Stadium.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Chris Clark played with the Michigan High School All Stars in 1984. They played the Illinois High School All Stars at Tiger Stadium. Chris was the MVP of the game throwing four no hit innings.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

MONROE COUNTY ALL STAR GAME - At the end of each season, two coaches are selected and they draft seniors from Monroe County schools. The game is played at one of the local high school fields after the state finals. The following players/coaches have been selected to represent Carlson.
